Key Match Events: Marko Arnautovic scored the opening goal for Austria by rifling a shot in off the underside of the bar.
Alexander Sorloth equalized for Norway from a set-piece delivery by Julian Ryerson.
Marko Arnautovic scored a penalty for Austria after Christoph Baumgartner was fouled by Andreas Hanche-Olsen.
Philipp Lienhart scored Austria's third goal with a towering header from a Romano Schmid corner.
Stefan Posch scored Austria's fourth goal with a header from a Marcel Sabitzer cross.
Michael Gregoritsch scored Austria's fifth goal from another Marcel Sabitzer cross.
Pre-Game Insights: Erling Haaland wore the captain’s armband for Norway in the absence of Martin Odegaard.
Post-Match Reflections: Austria's victory drew them level on points with Norway at the top of UEFA Nations League Group B3.
This win was Austria's second victory in the last seven meetings between the sides.
Norway experienced their first defeat in five matches without Martin Odegaard.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The floodlights temporarily failed during the match, plunging the stadium into darkness.
Marko Arnautovic was named Flashscore Man of the Match.
